Update some attributes of a package repository.

<%= available_since('16.11.0') %>

<p class='http-request-heading'>HTTP Request</p>

`PUT /go/api/admin/repositories/:repo_id`

All the following properties must be specified.
<aside class="notice">
  <strong>Important:</strong>
  Please note that this API allows to edit the configuration of package repository which contains packages.
</aside>


<aside class="notice">
  <strong>Note:</strong>
  The update package repository API requires that you submit the <code>If-Match</code>
  header with the latest ETag value that is representative of the current
  package repository config resource.
  <br/><br/>
  This is required in order to avoid the "lost update" problem, where a client
  `GET`s a resource's state, modifies it and `PUT`s it back to the server, while
  another user has modified the state of the package repository config, leading to a
  conflict.
</aside>

